hej team:
there is a way to re-create a dvd in case the dvd´s got a corrupt file IFO so you gotta do this:

1- save the four VOB files. I mean: VOB1, VOB2, VOB3 y VOB4.
2-Use VobEdit v0.6 (it´s free to dowload it)
3-This program gets the four VOB files turn into one continuous track.
4-Later you have to use IfoEdit v0.971 (it´s free too)
5-This program re-creates the IFO files with their BUP files. (BUP are back-up of IFO)
The result is a folder called VIDEO_TS including the files IFO; BUP and VOB in perfect condition.

Finally, you gotta burn this VIDEO_TS folder with NeroBurning to get AUDIO_TS and VIDEO_TS into a physical dvd, that´s all. Just try it.
